It wouldn't necessarily have to be a fetish. People/anthros would generally accept it as "That's what makes them different. <shrug>" for those who enjoy being with humans. Of those who are accepting, a segment would find it somewhat kinky/fetishy.

A lot depends on the world building for that universe. In our real world, a lot of animals sweat, but from very restricted zones (paws, for example). And some, such as horses, sweat more or less like humans. So, it would probably not be all that weird for just those examples.

Digging into the evolutionary world building, it could also be a "feature" that most anthros develop on their way toward sapience. Survival of the species might depend upon developing larger & different areas where anthros sweat. Maybe not to the degree that humans do, but maybe well beyond what we expect of most animals in our real world.

An anthro world populated with a lot of species might have quite a bit of variation, running from nearly not sweating at all (species who run a strong risk of overheating) through various degrees all the way to human-tier that sweat from nearly their entire skin surface. Species who had to develop cooling skills for their climate & activity level. There's a pretty rich area here to mine for various cultural standards & interactions based upon hygiene, scent, etc.
